# PART 1 \'97 BUILD AN INTEGRATIONS HUB\
\
Create a first-class Integrations Hub for every account / org.\
\
## Core requirement\
Every account should be able to connect one or more external platforms.\
\
Examples to support in architecture and prioritization:\
- Flight Schedule Pro\
- Flight Circle\
- MyFBO\
- TalonETA / TalonRMS\
- Avianis\
- FL3XX\
- Leon\
\
## Research-based prioritization\
Treat the following as priority connectors because they are common and/or publicly show meaningful integration capability:\
\
### Flight schools / clubs / training / rentals\
1. Flight Schedule Pro\
2. Flight Circle\
3. MyFBO\
4. TalonETA / TalonRMS\
\
### Part 91 / charter / Part 135 / business aviation\
5. Avianis\
6. FL3XX\
7. Leon\
\
## Integration architecture\
Build a provider abstraction:\
\
- `IntegrationProvider`\
- `SchedulingProvider`\
- `AircraftSyncProvider`\
- `UsageSyncProvider`\
- `WebhookProvider`\
- `CredentialVaultAdapter`\
\
Concrete provider examples:\
- `FlightScheduleProProvider`\
- `FlightCircleProvider`\
- `MyFboProvider`\
- `TalonProvider`\
- `AvianisProvider`\
- `Fl3xxProvider`\
- `LeonProvider`\
\
Do NOT hard-code the app around one vendor.\
\
