\
# PART 2 \'97 WHAT EACH CONNECTOR MUST DO\
\
For each connector, support as much as the provider allows through public API, webhooks, partner API, or adapter polling.\
\
## Minimum sync goals\
Each provider should attempt to retrieve:\
\
### Organization/account-level\
- connected account metadata\
- external org/account id\
- sync status\
- last sync timestamp\
\
### Aircraft-level\
- external aircraft id\
- tail number / registration\
- make\
- model\
- serial number if available\
- aircraft status\
- base/home airport if available\
- active/inactive state\
\
### Usage / schedule / dispatch-level\
- latest tach or equivalent usage field if available\
- latest hobbs if available\
- latest airframe time if available\
- reservation data\
- flight block time / flight activity if available\
- out/in times if available\
- dispatch/check-in/check-out data if available\
- maintenance grounding / out-of-service states if available\
\
### Delta sync\
- pull only changed aircraft / reservations / utilization records after prior sync when supported\
- otherwise poll intelligently\
\
### Webhooks\
- use webhooks when available\
- fall back to polling when not available\
\
