# PART 3 \'97 TACH / TIME SYNCHRONIZATION LOGIC\
\
The main business goal is reminders tied to current aircraft utilization.\
\
## Build a normalized aircraft usage ledger\
Do NOT trust one source blindly.\
Create a normalized usage model:\
\
- aircraft_id\
- source_type\
- source_provider\
- source_record_id\
- usage_timestamp\
- tach_value\
- hobbs_value\
- airframe_time\
- engine_time if available\
- block_time\
- flight_time\
- reliability_score\
- raw_payload\
- ingested_at\
\
## Source precedence strategy\
Implement source precedence and reconciliation:\
\
1. manually reviewed maintenance/document evidence can establish hard maintenance events\
2. high-confidence scheduling/dispatch sync updates current usage state\
3. registry data provides aircraft identity, not current usage\
4. AI-derived usage from documents can supplement but must not silently override higher-confidence live operational data\
\
## Current usage state\
Maintain a derived aircraft current-usage snapshot:\
- current tach\
- current hobbs\
- current airframe total time\
- source of truth\
- last updated from\
- confidence / trust score\
\
## Conflict handling\
If two sources disagree:\
- do not silently overwrite\
- record conflict\
- show conflict banner in aircraft admin view\
- apply precedence rules\
- create review task if discrepancy exceeds threshold\
\
---\
