# PART 4 \'97 AUTO-IMPORT AIRCRAFT FROM CONNECTED SYSTEMS\
\
When a customer connects a scheduling platform:\
\
1. fetch aircraft list from provider\
2. match existing aircraft in myaircraft.us by tail number first\
3. if no match, offer import/create flow\
4. enrich aircraft record with provider metadata\
5. connect aircraft record to provider source id\
6. continue background sync\
\
## Matching rules\
Primary:\
- tail number / N-number exact match\
\
Secondary:\
- serial number\
- make/model + tail normalization\
- manual confirmation if ambiguous\
\
Do not create duplicate aircraft silently.\
\
---\
\
# PART 5 \'97 REMINDERS INTELLIGENCE ENGINE\
\
Build a reminder engine that constantly evaluates all available aircraft data and automatically creates, updates, closes, or escalates reminders.\
\
## Inputs into reminder engine\
The reminder engine must continuously read from:\
\
1. aircraft registry / imported aircraft identity\
2. scheduling integrations\
3. utilization / tach / hobbs sync\
4. uploaded documents\
5. OCR / structured extraction from logbooks\
6. FAA AD catalog + aircraft applicability logic\
7. existing reminders\
8. manually entered overrides\
9. calendar/date-based expiration rules\
\
## Reminder engine outputs\
It must generate/update reminders for:\
- annual inspection\
- 100-hour inspection\
- progressive inspection if later supported\
- AD due / overdue / unknown compliance\
- recurring AD reinspection items\
- ELT battery due\
- transponder inspection due\
- static system inspection due\
- altimeter inspection due where applicable\
- VOR check reminders if tracked\
- registration expiration\
- airworthiness certificate / documentation review items as configured\
- pitot-static / IFR certification reminders\
- maintenance events derived from operating rules/templates\
- custom org-defined reminders\
- squawk/discrepancy reminders if integrated later\
\
## Important rule\
The platform should preload the full reminder catalog/template set, but individual reminders only activate when:\
- applicability is confirmed\
- likely applicability is detected\
- a document indicates it exists\
- a provider sync indicates it is relevant\
- a date/time/tach threshold is met\
\
---\
\
# PART 6 \'97 FAA AD AUTO-GENERATION\
\
Users should not manually build their AD reminders one by one.\
\
## Build FAA AD pipeline\
Create:\
- `AdCatalogProvider`\
- `AircraftApplicabilityEngine`\
- `AdEvidenceMatcher`\
- `AdReminderOrchestrator`\
\
## Workflow\
1. obtain aircraft identity and configuration\
2. fetch or refresh AD catalog data from official FAA-accessible sources or approved ingestion source abstraction\
3. evaluate likely applicability against aircraft and installed components\
4. create `aircraft_ad_status` records\
5. generate reminders automatically\
6. when logbooks are uploaded, detect AD references and match them to catalog records\
7. update compliance status and reminder status automatically\
\
## Reminder states\
Each AD can be:\
- applicable\
- likely_applicable_needs_review\
- not_applicable\
- compliant\
- due_soon\
- overdue\
- unknown_compliance\
\
---\
\
# PART 7 \'97 LLM-DRIVEN DOCUMENT / REMINDER UNDERSTANDING\
\
There must be a constant intelligence layer watching uploaded documents and extracted maintenance entries.\
\
## Goal\
As documents are uploaded and parsed, the system should identify reminder-relevant events automatically.\
\
## Examples of document-derived reminder signals\
From logbooks and records, detect:\
- annual inspection signoff\
- 100-hour inspection signoff\
- oil change intervals if configured\
- ELT battery replacement / expiration\
- transponder/static/altimeter inspection\
- AD compliance entries\
- component overhauls\
- engine/prop time references\
- recurring maintenance events\
- discrepancy closures\
- return to service language\
- due-by-date and due-by-hours language\
\
## Important behavior\
The LLM does NOT invent reminders.\
It helps classify and extract evidence.\
Canonical reminders are created by deterministic rules + normalized extracted evidence.\
\
## Required reminder evidence model\
Every reminder should be backed by:\
- source type\
- source document or integration event\
- aircraft id\
- evidence snippet\
- citation/page if document-based\
- provider payload ref if integration-based\
- confidence and reasoning\
\
